name: .BACKUPDB File Extension
summary: Learn about .BACKUPDB files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: Backup folder created by Apple Time Machine, a backup utility included with Mac OS X 10.5 (Leopard); named "Backups.backupdb" and is often the only folder on the backup drive.

content: Because Time Machine uses the "backupdb" folder for storing incremental backups, it should not be modified by the user. Instead, use the Time Machine application to view backups and restore files.
